# 10. Example: Two Different Students

## Student A

```text
Goal:
Machine Learning

Weakness:
Linear Algebra

Level:
Beginner

Preference:
Short Videos
```

The Recommendation Engine may select:

```text
Beginner Linear Algebra Video
```

---

## Student B

```text
Goal:
Natural Language Processing

Strength:
Linear Algebra

Interest:
NLP

Preference:
Articles
```

The Recommendation Engine may select:

```text
Transformer Architecture Article
```

Both students ask:

> "What should I study today?"

The prompt is identical.

The recommendation changes because:

```text
Digital Twin A ≠ Digital Twin B
```

Therefore:

```text
Recommendation A ≠ Recommendation B
```

This demonstrates:

> **Personalization is caused by the architecture and learner state, not simply by changing the prompt.**

