Our proposed system is:

```text
              LEARNER
                 │
                 ▼
          DIGITAL TWIN
                 │
                 ▼
       RELEVANT LEARNER STATE
                 │
                 ▼
       SEARCH REQUIREMENTS
                 │
                 ▼
       RESOURCE RETRIEVAL
                 │
                 ▼
         RAW CANDIDATES
                 │
                 ▼
        VERIFICATION GATE
                 │
          ┌──────┴──────┐
          │             │
         PASS          FAIL
          │             │
          ▼             ▼
   VERIFIED RESOURCES  DISCARD
          │
          ▼
  RECOMMENDATION ENGINE
        (CODE)
          │
          ▼
       SCORE + RANK
          │
          ▼
    DECISION RECORD
          │
          ▼
  EXPLAINABILITY AGENT
          │
          ▼
        RESPONSE
```

With fallback support:

```text
External Search
      ↓ fails
Verified Resource Store
      ↓ unavailable
Alternative Source
      ↓ unavailable
Relax Constraints
      ↓ no result
Study Coach Clarification
      ↓
Search Again
      ↓ no result
Direct Teaching
```

And with background preparation:

```text
Learner Interaction
        ↓
Detect Future Learning Need
        ↓
Search in Background
        ↓
Verify Resources
        ↓
Store Resources
        ↓
Fast Future Recommendation
```

The main architectural principle is:

> **The Digital Twin provides personalized information about the learner. The Retrieval System finds possible learning resources. The Verification Gate ensures that resources are real and suitable. The code-based Recommendation Engine ranks the verified resources according to the learner's needs. The Explainability Agent explains the final decision. Fallback mechanisms ensure that the system fails safely instead of fabricating resources.**
